headline: Energy Stock With Earnings Seen Soaring 112% Clears Entry, Is Backed By This Top Fund
summary: Energy stock EQT has been outrunning the S&P 500 in 2025, and is now clearing a buy point. Earnings are seen surging in the years ahead.

headline: UBS Says It’s Time to Lean into These 2 Natural Gas Stocks — Here’s Why
summary: Despite all the talk about shifting toward ‘green’ or renewable sources, natural gas remains a valuable resource. The US, for example, is both a major consumer and a major producer of the cleanest-burning of the fossil fuels. In theory, the US can meet all of its gas needs from domestic production; in practice, due to limitations of infrastructure and transport, the country meets its needs through a combination of domestic production and imports, while simultaneously exporting gas for the world
